Mammoth North LLC
SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Mammoth North LLC (Mammoth North) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control
from Generation Sources Service (“Reactive Supply Service”) from the Mammoth North
generating facility (Mammoth North Facility).
Mammoth North is a solar generating facility located in Starke County, Indiana. The
Mammoth North Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities within the PJM
Interconnection, L.L.C. (“PJM”) region.
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Mammoth North’s revenue requirement for
Reactive Supply Service from the Mammoth North Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective
upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Mammoth North’s monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed
Capability Component. Payment to Mammoth shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM’s Open Access
Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $879,600.00.
The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $73,300.00
